title: Sit Ups
description:
Lie on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the floor, hip-width apart.
Place your hands behind your head, lightly supporting it, or cross your arms over your chest.
Engage your core and lift your upper body toward your knees, keeping your back straight and avoiding pulling on your neck.
Lower yourself back down with control to the starting position.

title: Burpee
description:
Burpee exercise: 1. Stand upright with your feet shoulder-width apart.  
2. Squat down and place your hands on the floor in front of you.  
3. Jump your feet back into a plank position.  
4. Perform a push-up, keeping your body straight.  
5. Jump your feet back to the squat position.  
6. Explosively jump into the air, reaching your arms overhead.  
7. Land softly and repeat.

title: Plank
description:
Start by lying face down on the floor.
Place your forearms on the ground with elbows directly under your shoulders, and keep your hands flat or clasped.
Lift your body off the floor, balancing on your forearms and toes, forming a straight line from head to heels.
Engage your core, keep your hips level, and avoid letting your back arch or your hips sag.
Hold this position for the desired amount of time while breathing steadily.

title: Mountain climbers
description:
Start in a high plank position with your hands shoulder-width apart.
Keeping your core engaged, alternately drive your knees toward your chest in a running motion.
Keep your back flat and hips level throughout the movement.
Maintain a steady pace while alternating legs.

title: Russian twists
description:
Sit on the floor with your knees bent and feet flat.
Lift your feet slightly off the ground and lean back slightly, keeping your back straight.
Clasp your hands together or hold a weight in front of your chest.
Twist your torso from side to side, touching the ground (or close to it) on each side.
Keep your core engaged throughout the movement.
